# Tooling & quality gates

## ESLint

- Use: `@typescript-eslint`, `eslint-plugin-react`, `eslint-plugin-react-hooks`, `eslint-plugin-import`, `eslint-plugin-unused-imports`.
- Enforce: no unused variables, no `console.log` in production (use `no-console` or strip in build), hooks rules, no default exports (optional), named exports only.

## Prettier

- Strict formatting to avoid noisy diffs; run on save or in pre-commit.

## Pre-commit (Husky + lint-staged)

- **tsc --noEmit** (type-check)
- **eslint** (lint)
- **prettier --check** (format check)

Broken code or formatting should not be committed; AI improves when these gates are in place.

## CI

- Consider: bundle analyzer in CI, typed API contracts shared with backend.
